main event: A civilian observed a silver, disc-shaped object moving west to east over Pennsylvania on July 12, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as bright, glowing, and metallic in appearance.
It was observed for around 45 minutes, during which it accelerated quickly and disappeared to the east.
Several other sightings of a similar object were reported in the area around the same time.
Law enforcement agencies were alerted and investigating the sightings.
The object was estimated to be at a very high altitude, around 80-90,000 feet.
